FBIS4-32054 "dreeu118_p_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 POLAND Strikers at Warsaw Steelworks Begin Sit-In Strikers at Warsaw Steelworks Begin Sit-In LD1806083594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 GMT 18 Jun 94 LD1806083594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network Polish BFN [Text] A sit-in began this morning at the board offices of the Lucchini Steelworks in Warsaw. Jacek Gasiorowski, cochairman of the Solidarity strike committee, said this form of protest will last until the board begins negotiations with the strikers. The dispute at the Lucchini-Warszawa Steelworks began on 9 June. The steelworkers are demanding a pay raise of 30 percent and that modernization of the steelworks be undertaken by the Italian owner. The strike has been organized jointly by Solidarity and the National Trade Union Alliance [OPZZ].
